import json, os
from pathlib import Path

nb = {
    "cells": [
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "# Distance from Shore, Seasonality, and Low-Oxygen Conditions in NYC Harbor\n",
                "\n",
                "**Research question:** Do warm-season, nearshore plankton-rich conditions in NYC Harbor correspond to more low-oxygen events than cooler, farther-from-shore conditions?\n",
                "\n",
                "**Working ecological interpretation:** chlorophyll is treated as a bulk plankton proxy. The notebook does not directly identify cyanobacteria or diatoms.\n",
                "\n",
                "**Operational hypothesis:**\n",
                "- summer observations closer to shore will tend to have higher chlorophyll values\n",
                "- higher chlorophyll and warmer water will tend to co-occur with lower bottom dissolved oxygen\n",
                "- winter observations will tend to show a different distance-from-shore pattern and fewer low-oxygen events\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Required Python features used\n",
                "\n",
                "- **Indexing / slicing**: selecting columns, filtering seasons, subsetting valid rows\n",
                "- **`numpy.where`**: creating season classes, chlorophyll flags, and low-oxygen flags\n",
                "- **`groupby`**: summarizing by month, season, and shoreline-distance class\n",
                "- **`matplotlib`**: generating maps and statistical plots\n",
                "- **Functions**: keeping repeated geospatial and plotting logic concise\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Import packages\n",
                "import pandas as pd\n",
                "import numpy as np\n",
                "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
                "import geopandas as gpd\n",
                "from pathlib import Path\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 130\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## File paths\n",
                "\n",
                "These paths assume the notebook is inside a GitHub repository and the data files are stored in a `data/` folder next to it or below it.\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Set file paths for the real project files\n",
                "water_fp = Path('data/NYS-Harbor-Data.csv')\n",
                "ny_shore_fp = Path('data/State_Shoreline.shp')\n",
                "nj_shore_fp = Path('data/NJ_State_Boundary.shp')\n",
                "\n",
                "print('Water CSV:', water_fp)\n",
                "print('NY shoreline:', ny_shore_fp)\n",
                "print('NJ polygon/boundary:', nj_shore_fp)\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Load the harbor dataset and inspect key columns\n",
                "\n",
                "The relevant confirmed fields from the CSV are:\n",
                "- `sampling_location`\n",
                "- `sample_date`\n",
                "- `top_sample_temperature_c`\n",
                "- `ctd_conductivity_temperature_depth_profiler_bottom_dissolved_oxygen_mg_l`\n",
                "- `top_active_chlorophyll_a_g_l`\n",
                "- `top_silica_mg_l`\n",
                "- `long`\n",
                "- `lat`\n",
                "\n",
                "Those field names were verified from the uploaded column listing.\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Load only the columns needed for this analysis\n",
                "use_cols = [\n",
                "    'sampling_location',\n",
                "    'sample_date',\n",
                "    'top_sample_temperature_c',\n",
                "    'ctd_conductivity_temperature_depth_profiler_bottom_dissolved_oxygen_mg_l',\n",
                "    'top_active_chlorophyll_a_g_l',\n",
                "    'top_silica_mg_l',\n",
                "    'long',\n",
                "    'lat'\n",
                "]\n",
                "\n",
                "df = pd.read_csv(water_fp, usecols=use_cols)\n",
                "df.head()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Rename columns to shorter working names and clean types\n",
                "df = df.rename(columns={\n",
                "    'sampling_location': 'site',\n",
                "    'sample_date': 'date',\n",
                "    'top_sample_temperature_c': 'temp_c',\n",
                "    'ctd_conductivity_temperature_depth_profiler_bottom_dissolved_oxygen_mg_l': 'bottom_do_mg_l',\n",
                "    'top_active_chlorophyll_a_g_l': 'chl_a',\n",
                "    'top_silica_mg_l': 'silica_mg_l',\n",
                "    'long': 'lon',\n",
                "    'lat': 'lat'\n",
                "})\n",
                "\n",
                "df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date'])\n",
                "df['month'] = df['date'].dt.month\n",
                "\n",
                "for c in ['temp_c', 'bottom_do_mg_l', 'chl_a', 'silica_mg_l', 'lon', 'lat']:\n",
                "    df[c] = pd.to_numeric(df[c], errors='coerce')\n",
                "\n",
                "df = df.dropna(subset=['temp_c', 'bottom_do_mg_l', 'chl_a', 'lon', 'lat'])\n",
                "df.head()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Build shoreline geometry\n",
                "\n",
                "The NY and NJ files are read together and dissolved into one shoreline reference layer. For this project, the nearest polygon edge is used as the shoreline-distance proxy.\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Load the NY and NJ boundary layers, then combine them\n",
                "ny_shore = gpd.read_file(ny_shore_fp)\n",
                "nj_shore = gpd.read_file(nj_shore_fp)\n",
                "\n",
                "shore = pd.concat([ny_shore, nj_shore], ignore_index=True)\n",
                "shore = gpd.GeoDataFrame(shore, geometry='geometry', crs=ny_shore.crs)\n",
                "\n",
                "shore.head()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Convert water observations into a GeoDataFrame and project both layers\n",
                "gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame(\n",
                "    df,\n",
                "    geometry=gpd.points_from_xy(df['lon'], df['lat']),\n",
                "    crs='EPSG:4326'\n",
                ")\n",
                "\n",
                "gdf = gdf.to_crs('EPSG:32618')\n",
                "shore = shore.to_crs('EPSG:32618')\n",
                "\n",
                "print('Observation count:', len(gdf))\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Define reusable helper functions\n",
                "def add_distance_to_shore(points_gdf, shore_gdf):\n",
                "    shore_union = shore_gdf.geometry.union_all() if hasattr(shore_gdf.geometry, 'union_all') else shore_gdf.unary_union\n",
                "    points_gdf = points_gdf.copy()\n",
                "    points_gdf['distance_to_shore_m'] = points_gdf.geometry.distance(shore_union)\n",
                "    return points_gdf\n",
                "\n",
                "def assign_flags(points_gdf):\n",
                "    points_gdf = points_gdf.copy()\n",
                "    points_gdf['season'] = np.where(points_gdf['month'].isin([12, 1, 2]), 'winter',\n",
                "                        np.where(points_gdf['month'].isin([6, 7, 8]), 'summer', 'transition'))\n",
                "    \n",
                "    seasonal_chl_q75 = points_gdf.groupby('season')['chl_a'].transform(lambda s: s.quantile(0.75))\n",
                "    points_gdf['bloom_flag'] = np.where(points_gdf['chl_a'] >= seasonal_chl_q75, 1, 0)\n",
                "    points_gdf['low_oxygen_3mg'] = np.where(points_gdf['bottom_do_mg_l'] < 3.0, 1, 0)\n",
                "    points_gdf['hypoxia_2mg'] = np.where(points_gdf['bottom_do_mg_l'] < 2.0, 1, 0)\n",
                "    \n",
                "    distance_cut = points_gdf['distance_to_shore_m'].median()\n",
                "    points_gdf['shore_bin'] = np.where(points_gdf['distance_to_shore_m'] <= distance_cut, 'nearshore', 'offshore')\n",
                "    return points_gdf\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Compute shoreline distance and assign categorical flags\n",
                "gdf = add_distance_to_shore(gdf, shore)\n",
                "gdf = assign_flags(gdf)\n",
                "\n",
                "gdf[['site', 'date', 'distance_to_shore_m', 'season', 'shore_bin', 'bloom_flag', 'low_oxygen_3mg']].head()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Monthly distance check\n",
                "\n",
                "This directly tests whether observations with stronger plankton signal tend to cluster closer to or farther from shore during different months.\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Summarize mean distance from shore by month\n",
                "monthly_distance = (gdf.groupby('month', as_index=False)\n",
                "                    .agg(mean_distance_m=('distance_to_shore_m', 'mean'),\n",
                "                         mean_chl=('chl_a', 'mean'),\n",
                "                         mean_temp=('temp_c', 'mean'),\n",
                "                         low_oxygen_freq=('low_oxygen_3mg', 'mean'),\n",
                "                         n=('site', 'size')))\n",
                "monthly_distance\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Seasonal and spatial summaries\n",
                "\n",
                "This compares summer and winter conditions in nearshore and offshore bins.\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Group by season and shoreline-distance class\n",
                "season_space = (gdf[gdf['season'].isin(['winter', 'summer'])]\n",
                "                .groupby(['season', 'shore_bin'], as_index=False)\n",
                "                .agg(mean_chl=('chl_a', 'mean'),\n",
                "                     mean_temp=('temp_c', 'mean'),\n",
                "                     mean_bottom_do=('bottom_do_mg_l', 'mean'),\n",
                "                     mean_silica=('silica_mg_l', 'mean'),\n",
                "                     low_oxygen_freq=('low_oxygen_3mg', 'mean'),\n",
                "                     hypoxia_freq=('hypoxia_2mg', 'mean'),\n",
                "                     mean_distance_m=('distance_to_shore_m', 'mean'),\n",
                "                     n=('site', 'size')))\n",
                "season_space\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Visualization 1: shoreline map with stations\n",
                "\n",
                "This is the multimodal element: water-quality observations plus GIS boundary data.\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Plot shoreline polygons and station points colored by low-oxygen flag\n",
                "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 7))\n",
                "shore.plot(ax=ax, color='none', edgecolor='black', linewidth=0.5)\n",
                "gdf.plot(ax=ax, column='low_oxygen_3mg', markersize=6, legend=True)\n",
                "ax.set_title('NYC Harbor stations and low-oxygen observations')\n",
                "ax.set_axis_off()\n",
                "plt.show()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Visualization 2: mean distance from shore by month\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Plot mean distance from shore by month\n",
                "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 4))\n",
                "plt.plot(monthly_distance['month'], monthly_distance['mean_distance_m'], marker='o')\n",
                "plt.xlabel('Month')\n",
                "plt.ylabel('Mean distance from shore (m)')\n",
                "plt.title('Mean observation distance from shore by month')\n",
                "plt.xticks(range(1, 13))\n",
                "plt.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
                "plt.show()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Visualization 3: chlorophyll, temperature, and bottom dissolved oxygen\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Compare seasonal-space structure across nearshore and offshore bins\n",
                "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(14, 4), sharex=True)\n",
                "vars_to_plot = [\n",
                "    ('mean_chl', 'Mean chlorophyll-a'),\n",
                "    ('mean_temp', 'Mean temperature (C)'),\n",
                "    ('mean_bottom_do', 'Mean bottom DO (mg/L)')\n",
                "]\n",
                "\n",
                "for ax, (v, lab) in zip(axes, vars_to_plot):\n",
                "    for shore_bin, marker in [('nearshore', 'o'), ('offshore', 's')]:\n",
                "        d = season_space[season_space['shore_bin'] == shore_bin]\n",
                "        ax.plot(d['season'], d[v], marker=marker, label=shore_bin)\n",
                "    ax.set_title(lab)\n",
                "    ax.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
                "\n",
                "axes[0].legend()\n",
                "plt.tight_layout()\n",
                "plt.show()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Visualization 4: low-oxygen frequency by season and shoreline-distance class\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Bar plot for low-oxygen frequency\n",
                "pivot_lo = season_space.pivot(index='season', columns='shore_bin', values='low_oxygen_freq')\n",
                "pivot_lo.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(7, 4))\n",
                "plt.ylabel('Fraction of observations with bottom DO < 3 mg/L')\n",
                "plt.title('Low-oxygen frequency by season and shoreline-distance class')\n",
                "plt.xticks(rotation=0)\n",
                "plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)\n",
                "plt.show()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Visualization 5: distance, oxygen, and chlorophyll relationship\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Scatter plot showing distance-to-shore vs bottom oxygen, colored by chlorophyll\n",
                "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 5))\n",
                "plt.scatter(gdf['distance_to_shore_m'], gdf['bottom_do_mg_l'], c=gdf['chl_a'], s=10)\n",
                "plt.xlabel('Distance from shore (m)')\n",
                "plt.ylabel('Bottom dissolved oxygen (mg/L)')\n",
                "plt.title('Distance from shore vs bottom dissolved oxygen')\n",
                "plt.colorbar(label='Top chlorophyll-a')\n",
                "plt.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
                "plt.show()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Optional silica check\n",
                "\n",
                "This does not prove dominance by any taxon, but it gives you one more seasonal chemical context variable.\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": None,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Plot seasonal mean silica by nearshore/offshore bin\n",
                "pivot_silica = season_space.pivot(index='season', columns='shore_bin', values='mean_silica')\n",
                "pivot_silica.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(7, 4))\n",
                "plt.ylabel('Mean silica (mg/L)')\n",
                "plt.title('Seasonal silica by shoreline-distance class')\n",
                "plt.xticks(rotation=0)\n",
                "plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)\n",
                "plt.show()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Final summary\n",
                "\n",
                "Fill this in after running the notebook.\n",
                "\n",
                "**Template:**\n",
                "\n",
                "- Mean observation distance from shore was highest in [months] and lowest in [months].\n",
                "- Summer nearshore observations had [higher/lower] chlorophyll and [higher/lower] low-oxygen frequency than summer offshore observations.\n",
                "- Winter observations had [higher/lower] chlorophyll and [higher/lower] bottom dissolved oxygen than summer observations.\n",
                "- The shoreline-distance plots [support / partly support / do not support] the claim that nearshore warm-season plankton-rich conditions correspond to more low-oxygen events.\n",
                "- Chlorophyll and silica provide proxy context only; this notebook does not directly identify cyanobacteria or diatoms.\n"
            ]
        }
    ],
    "metadata": {
        "kernelspec": {
            "display_name": "Python 3",
            "language": "python",
            "name": "python3"
        },
        "language_info": {
            "name": "python",
            "version": "3.x"
